"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010353","Home Office","false","2018-11-22","<p>The Home Office does not centrally collect information on offences under the Hunting Act 2004 and therefore the requested information on arrests and subsequent convictions is not held by the Home Office.</p><p>The enforcement of the Hunting Act is an operational matter for the police. This is in line with their duties to keep the peace, protect communities and prevent the commission of offences, working within the provisions of the legal framework set by Parliament.</p><p>It is for individual Chief Constables to determine how their resources are deployed and it is for locally elected Police and Crime Commissioners to hold their forces to account, including on how they tackle the crimes that matter most to residents and businesses in rural and urban areas alike.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","192915 ; 192916","2018-11-22T14:24:55.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010353/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010353/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-11-19","Hunting: County Durham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many cases of breaches of the Hunting Act 2004 were referred to the Crown Prosecution Service by Durham constabulary in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","192914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010354","Wales Office","false","2018-11-22","<p>Funding for Welsh language learning forms part of the training budget for staff in the Office of the Secretary of State for Wales. The training budget in each of the last 5 years was £15,000 per annum.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2018-11-22T15:28:59.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010354/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010354/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-11-19","Wales Office: Welsh Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how much funding he allocated to Welsh lessons for staff in his Department in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","192804"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010355","Wales Office","false","2018-11-22","<p>The strategy commits the UK Government to work with the devolved administrations to ensure that the work to implement the strategy is complementary and to share insights and learn from one another.</p>","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams",,"2018-11-22T15:17:58.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010355/answer","Biography information for Nigel Adams","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1010355/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-11-19","Loneliness: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what steps he is taking to incorporate the Prime Minister's cross-governmental loneliness strategy into the policy-formulation and decision-making processes of his Department.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","192805"
