"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007789","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-11-21","<p>There is no recent estimate of the number of public authority buildings between 250 and 1,000 square metres which are required to possess a Display Energy Certificate (DEC). The current number of DECs for buildings of between 250 and 1,000 square meters, including voluntary DECs, is 29,209.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-11-21T13:47:26.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007789/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007789/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1007789/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-11-15","Energy Performance Certificates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the number of buildings with a total floor area between 250 and 1,000 square metres which are required to possess a display energy certificate; and what proportion of those buildings are compliant to date.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","191856"
